
@startuml
class Student {
  -studentID: String
  -name: String
  -email: String
  -registeredCourses: List<Course>
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  -taID: String
  -name: String
  -email: String
  -teachingCourses: List<Course>
}

class Course {
  -courseCode: String
  -title: String
  -description: String
}

class Appointment {
  -appointmentID: String
  -date: Date
  -time: Time
  -duration: Integer
  -student: Student
  -teachingAssistant: TeachingAssistant
  -course: Course
}

Student "1" -- "0..*" Course : registered for
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Course : teaches
Appointment "1" -- "1" Student : requested by
Appointment "1" -- "1" TeachingAssistant : assigned to
Appointment "1" -- "1" Course : related to

note right of Appointment
  An appointment is always for one specific course and with one particular TA.
end note

note right of Student
  A student can only request an appointment for a course they are registered for.
end note

note right of TeachingAssistant
  A TA can only provide help for courses they are teaching.
end note
@enduml

### Explanation:
- **Student**: Has a list of registered courses and can request appointments for those courses.
- **TeachingAssistant**: Has a list of courses they teach and can be assigned to appointments for those courses.
- **Course**: Represents a course with a code, title, and description.
- **Appointment**: Links a student, a teaching assistant, and a course. It has details like date, time, and duration.

